{
  "text": "Columns (2)- (3), (5) However, despite the fact that the p-values of the Hansen and the difference-in-Hansen tests for instrument validity exceed the 'common sense' threshold of 0.25 [CITATION_1] ), the Arellano-Bond test suggests that lagged instruments are being made invalid through autocorrelation.",
